messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full HTTP request path
- /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}

All HTTP methods acceptable?
- false

Acceptable methods (based on the code)
- HEAD: false
- POST: false
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: true
- PATCH: false

Explanation
- The ManagerController class has no class-level @RequestMapping, so method-level paths are the full paths.
- The deleteEmployee method is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID}", method = RequestMethod.DELETE)
  which establishes the exact path /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID} and explicitly accepts only the DELETE method.
- Other HTTP methods seen in this controller (GET, POST, PUT) are mapped to the related path /printshops/{printShopID}/employees (without the {employeeID} segment) â€” they do not apply to the /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID} path.
- I evaluated acceptable methods strictly from the source code annotations, not from framework defaults (e.g., automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling), per your instruction.
